.so ../bk-macros
.TH "bk delta" "\*[BKVER]" %E% "\*(BC" "\*(UM"
.SH NAME
bk delta \- check in modified files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bk delta
.[B] \-acilpqu
.[OPTreq] \-y msg
.[OPTreq] \-Y file
.BKARGS
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
The
.B bk delta 
command is used to check in changes made to revision controlled files.
This command is fairly rich in features and is the preferred interface
for scripting.  For interactive checkins, 
.B "bk citool" 
is the preferred interface.
.SH OPTIONS
.if t .TP .75i
.if n .TP 1.25i
.B \-a
Normally, 
.B delta
wants a 
.B \-i
to add a file to the revision control system.  If this option is set,
then the following do the same thing:
.DS
bk delta -a newfile
bk delta -i newfile
bk new newfile
.DE
The usefulness of this option is more apparent when you consider having
a mixed list of files, some under revision control and some not.
.sp
When called with this option, bk delta will not create a null delta on
an edited, but unmodified file.
.sp
.tp
.B \-c
Take checkin comments from 
.if t .IR SCCS/c.filename .
.if n SCCS/c.<filename>.
It is an error if the c.file does not exist.
.tp
.OPTreq \-D file
Take diffs from
.if t .IR file .
.if n <file>.
.tp
.OPTreq \-E enc
Set file encoding (like admin).
.\" .tp
.\" .B \-h
.\" Invert sense of file's hash flag.
.tp
.OPTreq \-I file
Use init 
.ARG file
for meta data.
.tp
.B \-i
Initial check-in, create a new revision history.
.tp
.B \-l
Follow check in with a locked check out like bk get -e.
.tp
.OPTreq \-M mode
Set the permissions on the new delta to
.if t .IR mode .
.if n <mode>.
.tp
.B \-p
Print differences before prompting for comments.
.tp
.B \-q
Run silently.
.tp
.B \-u
Follow check in with an unlocked check out like bk get.
.tp
.OPTopt \-Y file
Prompt for one comment, then use it for all the files.
If
.ARG file
is specified then take the comments from that file.
.tp
.OPTreq \-y comment
Sets the revision comment to 
.if t .IR comment .
.if n <comment>.
.tp
.OPTreq \-Z alg
Compress stored s.file with 
.ARG alg
which may be:
.br
.ARG gzip
- like
.BR gzip (1) 
.br
.ARG none
-  no compression
.SH BUGS
